# 📖 Documentation: documentation/server/RESTART_SCRIPT_GUIDE.md
# 🔗 Related: documentation/server/README.md
# 
# 🆕 Version: 2.0.0 (September 1, 2025)
# 🛠️ Features: Smart mode detection, user choice, comprehensive logging, CACHE STATE PRESERVATION
# 
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT TROUBLESHOOTING NOTE:
# ====================================
# 
# If the default quick restart doesn't resolve your issue:
# 
# 1. Try complete restart mode:
#    ./restart complete
# 
# 2. If still having issues, use interactive mode:
#    ./restart --interactive
# 
# 3. For detailed diagnostics:
#    ./restart --verbose complete
# 
# 4. Check server logs:
#    tail -f logs/server_detailed.log
# 
# The complete mode performs comprehensive system analysis and
# automatic problem fixing that the quick mode doesn't include.
# 
# 🔧 RESTART MODES EXPLAINED
# ==========================
# 
# QUICK MODE (restart_server_quick.sh):
# --------------------------------------
# ⚡ Speed: Fast restart (5-10 seconds)
# 🎯 Use Case: Development, testing, minor changes
# ✅ Features:
#   - Stops server processes
#   - Cleans port conflicts
#   - Basic health checks
#   - Simple API testing
