# 
# COMPLETE MODE (restart_server_complete.sh):
# -------------------------------------------
# 🛡️ Stability: Comprehensive restart (30-60 seconds)
# 🎯 Use Case: Production, troubleshooting, major issues
# ✅ Features:
#   - Complete system analysis
#   - Database lock cleanup
#   - Cache and temp file cleanup
#   - Package dependency checks
#   - Route validation (23+ endpoints)
#   - Performance monitoring
#   - Automatic problem fixing
#   - Detailed error analysis
#   - Comprehensive logging
# ❌ Limitations:
#   - Slower startup time
#   - More resource intensive
# 
# 🧠 CACHE STATE PRESERVATION
# ===========================
# 
# The script now automatically detects and preserves the current cache state:
# 
# - DEVELOPMENT MODE: Cache TTL 10 seconds (fast development)
# - NO-CACHE MODE: Cache disabled (immediate updates)
# - PRODUCTION MODE: Cache TTL 5 minutes (performance)
# 
# Cache state is preserved across restarts unless explicitly changed with:
#   ./restart --cache-mode=development    # Force development mode
#   ./restart --cache-mode=no-cache      # Force no-cache mode  
#   ./restart --cache-mode=production    # Force production mode
# 
# DEFAULT BEHAVIOR:
# =================
# 
# The script now defaults to QUICK MODE for faster development cycles.
# Complete mode is only used when explicitly requested or when auto-detection
# determines it's necessary.
# 
# CACHE STATE IS ALWAYS PRESERVED unless explicitly changed.
# 
# SMART DETECTION LOGIC (when using --auto):
# ===========================================
# 
# The script can automatically choose the appropriate mode based on:
# 
# 1. SYSTEM HEALTH INDICATORS:
#    - Memory usage > 90% → Complete mode
#    - Recent errors in logs → Complete mode
#    - Database lock files → Complete mode
#    - Port conflicts → Quick mode
# 
# 2. USER ACTIVITY PATTERNS:
#    - Development session < 1 hour → Quick mode
#    - Production environment → Complete mode
#    - Recent code changes → Complete mode
# 
# 3. ERROR PATTERNS:
#    - Route failures → Complete mode
#    - Import errors → Complete mode
#    - Database errors → Complete mode
#    - Simple port conflicts → Quick mode
# 
# USAGE EXAMPLES:
# ===============
# 
# Default behavior (preserves current cache state):
#   ./restart                    # Quick mode + current cache state
# 
# Force specific mode:
#   ./restart quick             # Force quick mode + current cache state
#   ./restart complete          # Force complete mode + current cache state
#   ./restart auto              # Smart detection + current cache state
#   ./restart --quick           # Alternative syntax
#   ./restart --complete        # Alternative syntax
#   ./restart --auto            # Alternative syntax
# 
